This paper is about using machine learning methods to analyze biomedical data, which falls under the category of computational biology and bioinformatics. The paper specifically focuses on using genetic programming to automatically design machine learning pipelines for bioinformatics studies, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also involves working with large datasets, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.GR (Graphics).
